==English==

===Noun===

'''chirp'''

#(countable) A [[short]], [[sharp]] or [[high]] note or noise, as of a [[bird]] or [[insect]].

====Translations====
'''bird’s chirp'''
*Russian: [[чик-чирик]] (čik-čirík)

===Intransitive verb===

'''to chirp'''

#To make a shop, sharp, cheerful, as of small birds or crickets.
#to [[speak]] in a high-[[pitch]]ed [[staccato]]
#(slang) to [[insult]]

====Translations====
'''chirp like a bird'''
*Russian: [[куковать]] (kukovát’)

